Career counselors emphasize the importance of eye contact during interactions, and enthusiastic recruiters engage with students, with human resources teams taking notes on tablets. Event staff scan registrations and hand out lanyards at the entrance. International students queue for advice on visa sponsorship at a resume review table near the stage, and an alumni panel discusses preparation for technical interviews. As the event winds down, attendees use tablets at kiosks to upload resumes and fill interview sign-up sheets amidst the aroma of coffee and catered snacks. Volunteers collect leftover brochures and collapsed booths, with monitors displaying a link to a post-event survey.

Recruiters from tech firms, consulting companies, and nonprofits emphasize mission-driven career paths, jotting notes on tablets as career counselors advise maintaining eye contact during introductions. As the event concludes, students exit with tote bags filled with branded items, sharing experiences while volunteers clean up booths and gather leftover materials.
